2. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which are core topics in discrete mathematics. 
3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper involves algorithms for finding shortest paths and maximum flows in graphs, which are closely related to computational geometry problems. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper deals with graph theory and optimization, which are important topics in game theory. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper involves algorithms for solving optimization problems in graphs, which can be viewed as numerical analysis problems.
